{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/recipes/peruvian-charcoal-chicken","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>So last weekend when I went to get my usual Sunday treat from <a href=\"http://unionsquaredonuts.com/menu/\">Union Square Donuts</a>, I happened to stumble upon this hole-in-the-wall called <a href=\"http://machuchicken.com/machuchicken/\">Machu Chicken</a>.  I think \"stumble upon\" is the wrong word.  The moment I left the donut shop, I caught this smell of amazing charcoal goodness.  I didn't know what it was.  It could have been any meat, but man did it smell good.  When I finally tracked it down toe Machu Picchu Charcoal Chicken and Grill, I was surprised to find another party of three saying the exact same thing I did - that they had to find out where this amazing smell came from.</p>\n<p>I went in and this place wasn't really that big.  The decor reminded me of an outdoor Hawaiian bar, which can be rather fun.  Anyhow, there were a ton of Peruvian dishes on the menu and even a drink called chica morada, which is made with purple corn.  But even with the abundance of choice, I went straight for their signature - the charcoal chicken, and man, did I make the right choice.  I knew I had to go home and find a recipe.</p>\n<p>My recipe was adapted from <a href=\"http://www.seriouseats.com/recipes/2012/08/peruvian-style-grilled-chicken-with-green-sauce-recipe.html\">Serious Eats Peruvian Style Grilled Chicken</a>.  Now I baked this chicken, which I'll have to admit, took away that amazing charcoal goodness, but the spice rub for this recipe is amazing and I'll be happy to make it a part of any of my meals.  Maybe I'll try this again in the summer when I have the charcoal grill out.</p>\n<h4 id=\"grind-spices-in-mortar-and-pestle-or-mixer\"><a href=\"#grind-spices-in-mortar-and-pestle-or-mixer\" aria-label=\"grind spices in mortar and pestle or mixer permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Grind Spices in Mortar and Pestle (or Mixer)</h4>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 691px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/487154e564d8a688086015bbb7fcc0fd/bb402/64-2.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.71490593342982%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"64 2\" title=\"64 2\" src=\"/static/487154e564d8a688086015bbb7fcc0fd/bb402/64-2.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/487154e564d8a688086015bbb7fcc0fd/90185/64-2.jpg 450w,\n/static/487154e564d8a688086015bbb7fcc0fd/bb402/64-2.jpg 691w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 691px) 100vw, 691px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n#### Spice Paste\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 691px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/59a32318f27c37ced1aec2aea0a49f29/bb402/64-3.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.71490593342982%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"64 3\" title=\"64 3\" src=\"/static/59a32318f27c37ced1aec2aea0a49f29/bb402/64-3.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/59a32318f27c37ced1aec2aea0a49f29/90185/64-3.jpg 450w,\n/static/59a32318f27c37ced1aec2aea0a49f29/bb402/64-3.jpg 691w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 691px) 100vw, 691px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n#### Spread Spice Paste over Chicken Thighs\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 691px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/4caa1c6ef389781817430b5c5af7dc7f/bb402/64-4.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.71490593342982%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"64 4\" title=\"64 4\" src=\"/static/4caa1c6ef389781817430b5c5af7dc7f/bb402/64-4.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/4caa1c6ef389781817430b5c5af7dc7f/90185/64-4.jpg 450w,\n/static/4caa1c6ef389781817430b5c5af7dc7f/bb402/64-4.jpg 691w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 691px) 100vw, 691px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n#### Serve with [Yellow Rice](http://www.eastmeetskitchen.com/recipes/easy-yellow-rice.html)\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 691px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/7eef2d31fc72bd1ebb59f4d80ad426c1/bb402/64-5.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.71490593342982%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"64 5\" title=\"64 5\" src=\"/static/7eef2d31fc72bd1ebb59f4d80ad426c1/bb402/64-5.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/7eef2d31fc72bd1ebb59f4d80ad426c1/90185/64-5.jpg 450w,\n/static/7eef2d31fc72bd1ebb59f4d80ad426c1/bb402/64-5.jpg 691w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 691px) 100vw, 691px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<section class=\"recipe\">\n<p><strong>Ingredients</strong></p></section>\n<p>(4-5 people)</p>\n<p>For the Chicken:\n- 8-10 chicken thighs\n- 4 teaspoons kosher salt\n- 2 tablespoons ground cumin\n- 2 tablespoons paprika\n- 1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper\n- 3 medium cloves garlic, minced (about 1 tablespoon)\n- 2 tablespoons white vinegar\n- 2 tablespoons vegetable or canola oil</p>\n<p><strong>Directions</strong></p>\n<ol><li>Grind together salt, cumin, paprika, pepper, and garlic </li><li>Add vinegar and oil to spices and mix until a paste is formed.  </li><li>Spread paste over chicken thighs</li><li>Bake for 40 minutes in a 400 degree Fahrenheit oven.  Chicken can also be grilled 10-15 minutes per side.</li></ol></section>","timeToRead":2,"excerpt":"So last weekend when I went to get my usual Sunday treat from Union Square Donuts, I happened to stumble upon this hole-in-the-wall calledâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"Peruvian Charcoal Chicken","image":{"feature":{"publicURL":"/static/64-1-deefb653e6c1e887f2ab4e2da14b6160.jpg","childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.5007751937984497,"src":"/static/deefb653e6c1e887f2ab4e2da14b6160/b17c1/64-1.jpg","srcSet":"/static/deefb653e6c1e887f2ab4e2da14b6160/00e5e/64-1.jpg 200w,\n/static/deefb653e6c1e887f2ab4e2da14b6160/1a903/64-1.jpg 400w,\n/static/deefb653e6c1e887f2ab4e2da14b6160/b17c1/64-1.jpg 800w,\n/static/deefb653e6c1e887f2ab4e2da14b6160/14b04/64-1.jpg 968w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}},"feature_video":null,"date":"2014-04-17","categories":["recipes"],"tags":["recipes","meats","Peru","Pervian","charcoal","chicken"]},"fields":{"slug":"/recipes/peruvian-charcoal-chicken","date":"2014-04-16T23:00:00.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/recipes/peruvian-charcoal-chicken","nextslug":"/blog/a-4-pizza","prevslug":"/recipes/dulce-de-leche-coconut-tres-leches"}}}